final_output_text: 1. To underline text in OneNote, you will first need to locate the text you wish to underline. This can be done by clicking on the text with your mouse cursor.

2. Once you have located the text, you will need to right-click on it. This will bring up a context menu with various options.

3. From the context menu, click on the "Home" tab. This tab is usually located at the top of the screen and is often represented by a house icon.

4. Within the "Home" tab, you will see a group of buttons. Click on the "Font" button, which is usually represented by a font icon.

5. Within the "Font" group, click on the "Underline" button. This button is usually represented by a underline icon.

6. Clicking on the "Underline" button will underline the selected text.

Alternatively, you can also underline text by highlighting it and then using the keyboard shortcut. To do this:

1. Select the text you wish to underline by clicking and dragging your mouse cursor over it.

2. Press the "U" key on your keyboard while holding down the "Ctrl" key (Windows) or "Command" key (Mac).

3. Release the "Ctrl" or "Command" key and the text will be underlined.

